WEBVTT

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:13.000
When I’m at home, for example, peeling cucumbers — especially cucumbers, because they’re soft —

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:16.000
the problem is that you can’t really feel your strength.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:19.000
I can do it, but sometimes I crush them.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:23.000
So with this, after a while, I’ll get feedback through vibration and I’ll be able to stop.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:28.000
I think that could be very beneficial in the long term.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:37.000
Peeling, picking up an apple — because sometimes you hold an apple in the palm of your hand and squeeze it, but you don’t feel it —

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:39.500
so you squeeze harder than you should.

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:43.000
The same goes for picking up a plastic bottle, for example, to avoid crushing it.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:47.000
But yes, at home, for daily activities, yes.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:56.000
If I were offered to change my prosthesis and it had that feature, I wouldn’t say no.

